defs.name: Train
defs.docs:
A train is a series of knots, each knot can be a terminal symbol.
 Train is used as argument of seq(), one_of() and none_of(),
 so that both b"byte string literal" and "string literal" can be accepted.

defs.name: parse
defs.docs: Apply the parser to parse input.

defs.docs: Convert parser result to desired value.

defs.name: opt

defs.name: repeat
defs.value: fn <R> (self, range: R) -> Parser<'a, I, Vec<O>>
defs.docs:
`p.repeat(5)` repeat p exactly 5 times
 `p.repeat(0..)` repeat p zero or more times
 `p.repeat(1..)` repeat p one or more times
 `p.repeat(1..4)` match p at least 1 and at most 3 times

defs.docs: Give parser a name to identify parsing errors.

defs.name: expect

defs.docs: Mark parser as expected, abort early when failed in ordered choice.

defs.name: empty
defs.docs: Always succeeds, consume no input.
